ENTRY       EC 5.5.1.24                 Enzyme
NAME        tocopherol cyclase;
            VTE1 (gene name);
            SXD1 (gene name)
CLASS       Isomerases;
            Intramolecular lyases;
            Intramolecular lyases (only sub-subclass identified to date)
SYSNAME     delta/gamma-tocopherol lyase (decyclizing)
REACTION    (1) delta-tocopherol = 2-methyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol  [RN:R07503];
            (2) gamma-tocopherol = 2,3-dimethyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol  [RN:R07502];
            (3) delta-tocotrienol = 6-geranylgeranyl-2-methylbenzene-1,4-diol  [RN:R10623];
            (4) gamma-tocotrienol = 6-geranylgeranyl-2,3-dimethylbenzene-1,4-diol [RN:R10624]
ALL_REAC    R07502 R07503 R10623 R10624
SUBSTRATE   delta-tocopherol [CPD:C14151];
            gamma-tocopherol [CPD:C02483];
            delta-tocotrienol [CPD:C14156];
            gamma-tocotrienol [CPD:C14155]
PRODUCT     2-methyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C15882];
            2,3-dimethyl-6-phytylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C15883];
            6-geranylgeranyl-2-methylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C20737];
            6-geranylgeranyl-2,3-dimethylbenzene-1,4-diol [CPD:C20738]
COMMENT     The enzyme has been described from plants and cyanobacteria. It has similar activity with all four listed benzoquinol substrates. Involved in the biosynthesis of vitamin E (tocopherols and tocotrienols).
